<item>
            <title>[SOLR-34] WordDelimiterFilter exception</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-34</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When WordDelimiterFilter is set to generate*Parts=0 and catenate*Parts=0 (for either Number or Word), it throws an exception when encountering such a token in the token stream.  This might be uncommon, but it should be possible (for instance, to filter out all numbers).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
